a good working atmosphere in a young team.
What you do as a Head of Customer Due Diligence
You will be responsible for managing internationally the client facing departments that are responsible for managing the entire customer life cycle from onboarding to termination of the relationship.
In this role, you have a focus on business change management and you will work in close cooperation with the Business and Compliance to centralize and align the process and procedures on an international level within an organization.
The Head CDD will be responsible for the daily operational management of the different CDD departments in the different branches. In this role, you will be able to define priorities in the daily workload of the teams whilst considering the AML/ CTF risks. The role is unique and offers a challenging opportunity to join a young and international organization to expand its activities in the future.
Your team consists out of approximately 4 Team Leaders across the Netherlands, Belgium, Germany, and the Czech Republic. The Team Leads are responsible for coaching and managing the local CDD Analysts. You will report to the COO.
This is you:
You have extensive (at least 7-10 years) experience with managing client-facing departments;
You have a university degree (such as Business Administration, Economics), or equivalent extensive working experience;
You understand investment companies and have professional knowledge of AML/ CTF risks, the related processes, technology, and developments in this area;
You have affinity or interest in optimization of KYC/CDD processes through digitalization and automation;
You are fluent in English and Dutch (verbally and in writing);
You are a good communicator, being able to convey complex messages in a simple way to bring adherence to “why” change is required to achieve effective management of AML/ CTF risks;
You have extensive experience with stakeholder management;
You have excellent management skills; you discuss the strategic goals, mission, and vision with your team members and the strategic role they play in inspiring their teams;
You are excellent in inspiring and coaching your team members; you encourage them to use their talents and competencies to achieve the organization's goals;
You are confident, process-orientated, result-driven, and seeks to find innovative and new creative solutions for new and existing challenges;
You have organizational sensitivity and decisiveness; you feel comfortable making changes within the organization;
You are willing to travel several times a year.
