Catawiki's goal is to make special objects universally available. Our weekly auctions feature thousands of unusual, rare, and exceptional objects that you won't find in just any store.

What does the work involve?

Your goal is to delight our customers (Sellers and Buyers) by solving complex challenges, answering their questions and supporting them in solving their issues. The customer experience department plays a crucial role in driving the retention of customers, ensuring they come back to Catawiki again and again.

We have a broad variety of customers, from traders in exclusive Ferrari's to Antique Jewellery collectors, and everything in between. Occasionally, there might be a dispute between a seller and a buyer. It is your challenge to mediate between each customer and find a solution that works for both. In this interesting customer service job you will gain knowledge on issues relating to legal, marketing, finance and international trade. Aside from this you will:

Be responsible for making sure customer issues and questions are addressed and resolved in a correct and timely manner, via phone or email;
Answer questions from customers, and from your extensive communication with users you look out for possibilities for improvements in our services;
Manage disputes and complaints, finding the best solution for both parties;
Work together with other departments to improve the customer experience.

This is who you are

Customer service is totally your thing and you can communicate in a clear, customer-oriented manner. Customer satisfaction is your main goal. You try your utmost to find fitting solutions to all problems. You do this in a patient, clear and empathetic way with the aim of customer satisfaction.

You speak fluent Spanish + Portuguese and write flawlessly;
You have experience in a customer related role (hospitality business, receptionist, callcenter, tourism etc.)
You have a basic command of the English language;
You are available for 40 hours per week;
You can quickly switch between telephony and e-mail;
You are willing to work 2 days a week until 19.00 pm and are available for 2 weekends a month;
You are currently living in the Amsterdam surroundings;
You are willing to work on public holidays.

What we offer
Gross salary of 2000 euro gross per month, based on 40 hours per week;
Travel allowance if you are not living in Amsterdam;
Catawikians who are performing good will get stock options in our company after 12 months and with that become an owner of Catawiki;
A challenging job in a young, fast-growing, dynamic and international organisation;
Freedom and responsibility to organise your work efficiently and friendly colleagues who are willing to help you;
Yoga, healthy Friday, mindfulness;
Regular fun employee activities and drinks;
Excellent opportunities for career development towards sales, marketing or a lead agent role in the Customer Service department;
Lots of room to work on great ideas, and to learn and grow.


