Welcome to Lepaya

Our mission is to enable professionals across the globe to be more effective in their work and enjoy more happiness in life. Did you know that 85% of your effectiveness at work is determined by soft skills? To deliver on our mission, we deliver high impact soft skill training. Our training platform provides professionals with the more modern tools to develop themselves: online where possible, offline or face-to-face where that has more impact.

Why do we need you?

We are looking for someone that has passion for and experience in digital product development.
Over the past two years we have built a digital platform that supports and delivers our trainings through our own mobile app, and with integrations into tools like Slack or Microsoft Teams.

Right now, we are gearing up for another growth spurt. In the next couple of years we will roll out to numerous new countries and plan to serve even more clients. To do that we need to make sure that our platform and apps become even better, while we also make sure we can keep delivering this experience as more and more learners use our platform. Our product roadmap is ambitious and contains projects like creating a learner cockpit, personalizing the learning experience, scalable delivery, and many more. We need you to help us realize this roadmap and spot opportunities to enhance the roadmap.

Your role

Your role will be to help make our apps and platform better. You are part of the (digital) product development team and will report to the CPO. You will work closely together with our Product Owners and UX designers.
Your daily work will be to head several roadmap projects. We expect you to be very hands-on and pragmatic, and not just run a process. You will have to take these projects from the concept phase, come up with a solution and take it to a state from which the development team can start building the new features. In between, you have done the data analysis, customer research and combined these with a healthy dose of creativity and innovativity. You translate these solutions into clear requirements (epics and user stories) that the Tech Team can use to start actual technical development. Note: this role is not a customer service or customer representation role, experience in (digital) product development is required.

Specifically, what would we expect you to deliver over the next 6-12 months?
Set up a customer insights process in which we gather (automated) feedback from customers and learners every 3 weeks, the results of which are translated into user stories;
Analyze user behavior on our platform and based on this you have continuously improved our user flow leading to increasing our engagement metric by at least 20%;
You will lead and complete one to two roadmap initiatives per quarter in which you translate complex business problems to concrete requirements which are ready to be picked up by the development team;

In an ideal world, who would you be?
You have hands-on experience in developing a digital product;
You’re a critical thinker and a pragmatic contributor;
You like building new (digital) products and to be innovative in what you create;
You’re data driven, you value facts backed up by actual data over opinions;
You know how to drive a project forward, are independent in structuring, planning and executing projects;
You’ve experience in fast-paced and high-performing work environments;

We value capabilities over formal experience, yet what would we love to see on your resume?

4+ years of work experience (background at a strategy/management consulting firm is a plus);
Proven record in digital product development;
Master degree in relevant field;
Experience with handling data;

And of course, next to the challenge we offer, why is it amazing to work for Lepaya?

You will join an inspiring and dynamic environment;
You will participate in Lepaya’s own training curriculum;
We offer accelerated personal growth and career opportunities;
We offer an attractive compensation package;
And the best: participation in the Lepaya Work-To-Live schedule consisting of unlimited holidays & a free Friday every second week.

What is Lepaya?

Our mission is to enable professionals across the globe to be more effective in their work and enjoy more happiness in life. Did you know that 85% of your effectiveness at work is determined by soft skills? To deliver on our mission, we deliver high impact soft skill training. Our training platform provides professionals with the more modern tools to develop themselves: online where possible, offline or face-to-face where that has more impact.

We launched early 2018 and, the success of our approach is demonstrated by our rapidly expanding client-base - ranging from the most innovative and fast-growing scale-ups such as Bynder and Picnic, to global corporates such as ING, and L’Oreal.

We are now fully committed to rapid growth and international expansion, supported by a recent €5 mln Series A investment. This makes it the perfect time to step in. The new CX Specialist has the opportunity to work in a dynamic and entrepreneurial environment, where he/she plays a central role in achieving ambitious growth.

A word on diversity: at Lepaya, all we’re askin’ is a little respect! To us, it doesn’t matter where you were born, what you believe in, how old you are, what you look like, or who you love. We believe that different perspectives and backgrounds will actually lift Lepaya to new heights and increase our power of thinking. Our passion is to build a strong culture with respect for each other’s unique experiences, backgrounds, perspectives and skills. Join us, as there is a place for you here!

Interested?

Are you looking for a challenge with a lot of responsibility and learning opportunities? Be part of a fun international team? Work on an innovative solution for learning & development? Get in touch with us now! As soon as possible after we have received your application, we will contact you. If we like your profile, we will invite you for a first chat via video call with our People Manager to explain to you more about us, the role, as well as the specifics of the interview process for the role.

With your knowledge about anti-money laundering and terrorist financing, combined with your managerial and process-orientated skills, you bring the international CDD department of LYNX to the next level
“LYNX helps you invest in yourself"
"Working at LYNX means joining the LYNX family"
"The development opportunities make LYNX the best place to work"
This is what the employees say about LYNX and it is exactly what we want to offer: a relaxed and informal work environment where you can get the best out of yourself. At our office in the heart of Amsterdam, we work every day to offer both private and professional clients the best trading opportunities, with a fast, user-friendly, and reliable trading platform.
LYNX is looking for an experienced Head of Customer Due Diligence with an international focus (based in Amsterdam). You will be part of the AML organization in which we have organized all the activities from customer onboarding up to transaction monitoring.
This is what we offer:
This role at LYNX is the perfect opportunity to give your career in the financial world a boost. We offer:
A salary depending on your educational level and work experience;
a fixed 13th month;
8% holiday allowance;
a discretionary annual bonus based on company results;
pension scheme that is fully paid by LYNX;
lunch from our cook, beverages & fruit;
public transport travel allowance;
home office equipment;
continuous growth potential and a training budget of € 2,000 per year;
trips & activities with your colleagues (of course not many at the moment);
a good working atmosphere in a young team.
What you do as a Head of Customer Due Diligence
Your mission is to lead the international client facing departments by optimizing the teams, procedures, and work methods. The departments are responsible for managing the entire customer life cycle from onboarding to termination of the relationship. You are the direct report of four team leads who are responsible for approximately 80 employees spread over the four branches. You report directly to our COO and work closely together with our FEC specialist and Compliance.
In this role, you will focus on improving and aligning the CDD processes. Your first task is to review these processes, optimize them, and make sure the teams use the same methods & systems and deliver the same quality. This means, you have to make firm decisions from time to time and you are able to create support for that. You efficiently oversee the processes and ensure that the right people are allocated to the right tasks. The output of the teams is monitored by you on a daily basis and you create monthly reports to inform the COO about the progress.
Next to that, you will focus on reaching the full potential of the individual team leads and their teams. This means you provide training on substantive topics and you coach the team leads by having progress conversations on a regular basis. You will also be responsible for hiring new talent and optimizing the teams' talents and skills together with HR.
The focus words of this role are: change management, stakeholder management, optimization & people management. With your expertise on these topics, you are able to design this role in a way that brings LYNX to the next level of professionality.
This is you:
You have extensive (at least 7-10 years) experience with managing client-facing departments;
You have a university degree (such as Business Administration, Economics), or equivalent extensive working experience;
You understand investment companies and have professional knowledge of AML/ CTF risks, the related processes, technology, and developments in this area;
You have affinity or interest in optimization of KYC/CDD processes through digitalization and automation;
You are fluent in English and Dutch (verbally and in writing);
You are a good communicator, being able to convey complex messages in a simple way to bring adherence to “why” change is required to achieve effective management of AML/ CTF risks;
You have excellent management skills; you discuss the strategic goals, mission, and vision with your team members and the strategic role they play in inspiring their teams;
You are excellent in inspiring and coaching your team members; you encourage them to use their talents and competencies to achieve the organization's goals;
You have organizational sensitivity; you feel comfortable making changes within the organization.
For this role, it is required that you travel several times a year to our European branches.
Apply:
We are looking forward to your application! Please send us your current cv and cover letter in English to Ivanka Kramer (HR specialist). We strive to process your application within a week. The application process consists of two interviews and the interviews will be via Microsoft teams. The first interview will be with HR and the FEC Specialist, and the second interview will be with the Chief Operating Officer and the AML Compliance Officer.
About LYNX
The best choice for anyone who takes investing seriously
LYNX is an online broker established in 2006 that offers execution-only services to investors throughout Europe. Clients of LYNX can trade worldwide in stocks, options, forex, futures, and similar exchange-listed securities and derivatives via the IB platform. The focus of LYNX is in particular on the experienced and more active investor. LYNX has offices in four European cities (Amsterdam, Ghent, Berlin, and Prague), in which more than 60.000 customers are serviced across the Netherlands, Finland, Germany, Switzerland, Austria, Belgium, France, Czech Republic, Slovakia, and Poland. LYNX is supervised by the Autoriteit Financiële Markten (Authority Financial Markets, ‘AFM’) and De Nederlandsche Bank (Dutch Central Bank, ‘DNB’).
For the execution of orders and the holding of an investment account, an agreement stands with Interactive Brokers (IB). IB is a subsidiary of the IBKR Group (a US-based global player in the field of online brokerage), which is listed on NASDAQ and has a market capitalization of around $22 billion. Due to the collaboration with IB, investors can execute their orders against low commissions via a state-of-the-art platform with useful trading tools. The investment services that LYNX provides consist of receiving and forwarding orders to Interactive Brokers (hereinafter ‘IB’). This is referred to as an execution-only service.

